{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a1d4467c-0198-40a7-986d-a2ac87847c3f","content":"I can guide you on analyzing your `.dmp` file, though I don't have a specialized skill for dump **analysis** (only for dump **collection**).\n\nHere are your best options for analyzing the dump:\n\n### 1. **`dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform)\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\nUseful commands inside the analyzer:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack of the crashing thread\n- `pe` — print last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `threads` — list all threads\n- `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` — inspect specific threads\n\n### 2. **WinDbg** (Windows, most powerful)\nLoad the dump, then:\n- `.loadby sos clr` or `.loadby sos coreclr`\n- `!pe` — print exception\n- `!clrstack` — managed stack\n- `!analyze -v` — automatic crash analysis\n\n### 3. **lldb + SOS** (Linux/macOS)\n```bash\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n# or\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\n```\n\n---\n\n**Want me to try analyzing it now?** If so, upload or provide the path to the `.dmp` file and I'll run `dotnet-dump analyze` on it (if the tool is available in this environment).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d71f93a2-653a-4b22-a36e-c4e108eb3ccf","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file and wants to analyze it. Let me check if there's a relevant skill available for this. Looking at the available skills:\n\n- `dump-collect` - This is for *collecting* crash dumps, NOT analyzing them. The description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\"\n\nNone of the available skills are designed for analyzing dump files. Let me help the user directly with guidance on how to analyze their dump file.\n\nLet me check what tools are available in the environment first.","outputTokens":493,"requestId":"2C44:1801E:15D871B:18D0324:69F94EDB"},"id":"8f5